{
  "text": "In archetype number one, represented by tarot card number one, the matrix of the mind seems to have to me, seems to have four basic parts to the complex looking at the card, we have first the most obvious the magician as a part, then what seems to be an approaching star, a stark or similar bird. It seems to be in a cage. On top of the cage we have something that is very difficult to discern. Am I in any way correct on this analysis? I am you are competent at viewing pictures. You have not yet grasped the nature of the matrix of the mind as a fully as is reliably possible upon a contemplation. We would note that the representations drawn by priests were somewhat distorted by acquaintance with and a dependence upon the astrologically based teachings of the Accaldees.",
